  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">School construction project in Western Uganda, Butembe, Jinja District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project activities include: design the plan for school and well constructions and oversee their construction; determine the well location, its depth, and the construction solution; acquiring a construction permit from the government; and establishing a local Project Monitoring Committee and a Parent Teacher Association that will be engaged in monitoring the progress of school and well construction activities and support the school&#x2019;s operations and activities in order to prepare them for its maintenance and sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to build a secondary school (S1 &#x2013; S4) that will accommodate approximately 240 students at a time.  A well and rainwater harvesting system will be also built.  A Parent Teacher Association will be formed to ensure school&apos;s sustainability.  IOCC has constructed and set-up two secondary schools in Gulu and Lwemiyaga since 2009 and both schools are fully operational.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ugandan secondary school children from Butembe, Jinja District, Uganda</narrative>
  </description>
